  "prompt": "How did Vodafone get its name?",
  "response": "Vodafone's name is derived from two words: \"Voice\" and \"Data.\" Additionally, the \"Fone\" part of the name is a playful twist on the word \"phone,\" emphasizing the company's focus on telecommunications. The name was chosen to reflect the company's initial focus on providing voice and data services over mobile networks. Vodafone was established in 1984 as a subsidiary of Racal Electronics, and it became an independent company in 1991.",
